{"questionId":"35029966","questionHtml":"<p>Hence find the total amount of antibiotic, in mg, that Ted receives during the first <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span> days.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{20\\left( {1 - {{0.5}^{10}}} \\right)}}{{1 - 0.5}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>20</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>0.5</mn>\n              </mrow>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>10</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>0.5</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)(A1)(ft)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong> for substitution into sum of a geometric sequence formula, <strong><em>(A1)(ft)</em></strong> for correct substitution.<br> Follow through from their <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{u_1}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span> in part (d)(i), if 0 &lt; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span> &lt; 1. Follow through from their <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span> in part (d)(ii) but only if <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\">\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span> is a positive integer.</p>\n<p>40.0&nbsp; (39.9609…) (mg)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)<em>(G2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35029966","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.T_4d.iii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the total amount of antibiotic, in mg, that Ted receives during the first k days.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Use of technology to solve systems of linear equations and polynomial equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}